place.name: DUNTON
place.gazetteerText: DUNTON-CUM-DOUGHTON, a parish in Walsingham district, Norfolk; 3 miles W by -N of Fakenham r-station. Post town, Fakenham. Acres, 1, 721. Real property, £2, 125. Pop., 126. Houses, 28. The living is a vicarage in the dio. of Norwich. Value, £161. Patron, the Lord Chancellor. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
